<p>I'm figuring out how can I save the values that are entered in the input text box inside <code>ng-repeat</code> on a single click of a button.I have seen examples like this <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11752977/angularjs-ng-model-scope-in-ng-repeat-is-undefined">getting values from text box</a> that lets user to save each text box individually. Below is a sample code:</p>  <pre><code>$scope.items=[1,2,3,4]  &lt;div ng-repeat="item in items"&gt; &lt;input type="text" ng-model=item.id&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;button type="button" ng-click="saveAllValues()"&gt;Save&lt;/button&gt; </code></pre>